  "texts": [
    "In a similar sense, DeepONets have been applied for the local analysis [442], whereas the global analysis is performed with a finite element solver.",
    "Both are conducted in an alternating fashion until convergence is reached.",
    "OptimizationOptimization is a fundamental task within computational mechanics and therefore addressed separately.",
    "It is not only used to find optimal structures, but also to solve inverse problems.",
    "Generally, the task can be formulated as minimizing a cost function C with respect to parameters λ."
  ]
